(442, '_transient_feed_c47db4c963e2d6948a299a85f4c71991', 'a:4:{s:5:\"child\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:3:\"rss\";a:1:{i:0;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:7:\"version\";s:3:\"2.0\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:7:\"channel\";a:1:{i:0;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:48:\"WordPress.org Forums » [W3 Total Cache] Support\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:57:\"https://wordpress.org/support/plugin/w3-total-cache/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"language\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5:\"en-US\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:13:\"lastBuildDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"Fri, 24 Dec 2021 05:43:27 PST\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:9:\"generator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:36:\"https://bbpress.org/?v=2.7.0-alpha-2\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"item\";a:30:{i:0;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:2:{s:0:\"\";a:5:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:26:\"Cache specific SQL queries\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:63:\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/cache-specific-sql-queries/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"Thu, 23 Dec 2021 10:22:00 PST\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:63:\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/cache-specific-sql-queries/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:4:\"true\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1159:\"<p>Replies: 1</p>\n						<p>Hi Marko,</p>\n<p>great plugin! Really what I wanted.<br />\nI have a specific question about MySQL caching:</p>\n<p>I have a page which ahs a lot of components and plugins activated.<br />\nI see in Query Monitor, that on nearly every page load, some specific repetitive SQL queries are ran by those plugins, which ALWAYS return the same results (I can assure that because they simply read configurations done by the admin and we never change those parts).</p>\n<p>My idea is:<br />\nLog the sql queries which are ran, identify them by md5&#8217;ing the SQL string, count how often than ran, and than cache specific queries, i.e. the results of $wpdb-&gt;query()/get_results().</p>\n<p>Can the plugin already do so?<br />\nI mean, I have already written my own code which logs all wpdb-queries (SAVEQUERIES) with md5 and run-counter. </p>\n<p>I just do not know where to hook into to make sure that calls to wpdb are avoided because results are taken from a file-cache&#8230; </p>\n<p>Seems this can be done only using wpdb dropin, but W3TC is using this already. So is it possible to achieve that functionality using W3TC?</p>\n<p>Thanks</p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"sx1001\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:1;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:2:{s:0:\"\";a:5:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:157:\"&lt;span class=&quot;resolved&quot; aria-label=&quot;Resolved&quot; title=&quot;Topic is resolved.&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;Can&amp;#8217;t disable minification\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:62:\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/cant-disable-minification/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"Thu, 23 Dec 2021 02:48:52 PST\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:62:\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/cant-disable-minification/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:4:\"true\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:917:\"<p>Replies: 4</p>\n						<p>Hi and thanks for the great plugin,</p>\n<p>I simply can&#8217;t disable the minification unless I switch off the page caching as well. </p>\n<p>If I have Page Cache ON and Minify OFF in the general settings, purge all the caches including the DIVI one, I get first and second page load OK but the third one contains references to W3TC minified files that are not wanted nor generated (404 errors). Tested on two sites on browser (networking panel, cache disabled). </p>\n<p>Thanks, Pavel.</p>\n\n\n<ul id=\"bbp-topic-revision-log-15190670\" class=\"bbp-topic-revision-log\">\n\n	<li id=\"bbp-topic-revision-log-15190670-item-15190745\" class=\"bbp-topic-revision-log-item\">\n		This topic was modified 1 day, 2 hours ago by <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/support/users/pumpaxxl/\" title=\"View PumpaXXL&#039;s profile\" class=\"bbp-author-link\"><span  class=\"bbp-author-name\">PumpaXXL</span></a>.\n	</li>\n\n</ul>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"PumpaXXL\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:2;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:2:{s:0:\"\";a:5:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:24:\"W3TC Image Service Speed\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:61:\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/w3tc-image-service-speed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"Wed, 22 Dec 2021 03:01:52 PST\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:61:\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/w3tc-image-service-speed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:4:\"true\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:860:\"<p>Replies: 4</p>\n						<p>I enabled the extension few days ago and behaviour / performance are really neglible at the moment:</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://ibb.co/WzjV9JN\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"><img src=\"https://i0.wp.com/i.ibb.co/WzjV9JN/w3tc-image-service.jpg?ssl=1\" alt=\"w3tc-image-service\" border=\"0\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" /></a></p>\n<p>It is not clear what I should do to convert all the existing images.</p>\n<p>Every time I click on <em>Convert all images</em>, after some dozens of seconds, I receive <em>Failed to retrieve a response. Please reload the page to try again</em> error.</p>\n<p>And every time I check again <em>Processing</em> count is 0.</p>\n<p>Not clear if I have to repeat this trial and error manual activity forever to complete the conversion or it is expected a background process after the initial request online.</p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"emilianomaina\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:3;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:2:{s:0:\"\";a:5:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:24:\"Testing CloudFront Fails\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:61:\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/testing-cloudfront-fails/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"Tue, 21 Dec 2021 11:15:58 PST\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:61:\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/testing-cloudfront-fails/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:4:\"true\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:362:\"<p>Replies: 1</p>\n						<p>If I test a CloudFront distribution backed by S3, it checks to see if the origin exists, but since CloudFront uses the region-specific endpoint as the origin, it fails with:</p>\n<p>&#8220;Error: Distribution for origin &#8220;XXXXXXXX.s3.amazonaws.com&#8221; not found.&#8221;</p>\n<p>Any guidance? Is this just the test that fails?</p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5:\"dlahn\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:4;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:2:{s:0:\"\";a:5:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:75:\"Unnecessary Image Service query in wp-admin even if the Service is disabled\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:112:\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/unnecessary-image-service-query-in-wp-admin-even-if-the-service-is-disabled/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"Tue, 21 Dec 2021 07:54:03 PST\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:112:\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/unnecessary-image-service-query-in-wp-admin-even-if-the-service-is-disabled/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:4:\"true\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:829:\"<p>Replies: 2</p>\n						<p>Hi I noticed, that when loading the multimedia library in wp-admin with the Image Service disabled, a query does still run looking for the meta key. </p>\n<p>wp_postmeta.meta_key = &#8216;w3tc_imageservice_file&#8217;</p>\n<p>This query can be slow on large site and with the service disabled it&#8217;s unnecessary. I didn&#8217;t check if it runs on other sites too. Could this be improved? Thanks!</p>\n\n\n<ul id=\"bbp-topic-revision-log-15185050\" class=\"bbp-topic-revision-log\">\n\n	<li id=\"bbp-topic-revision-log-15185050-item-15185056\" class=\"bbp-topic-revision-log-item\">\n		This topic was modified 2 days, 21 hours ago by <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/support/users/glashsix/\" title=\"View selycha&#039;s profile\" class=\"bbp-author-link\"><span  class=\"bbp-author-name\">selycha</span></a>.\n	</li>\n\n</ul>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"selycha\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:5;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:2:{s:0:\"\";a:5:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:39:\"W3 Total Cache Wiped Out My Entire Site\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:76:\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/w3-total-cache-wiped-out-my-entire-site/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"Mon, 20 Dec 2021 21:51:27 PST\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:76:\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/w3-total-cache-wiped-out-my-entire-site/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:4:\"true\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:514:\"<p>Replies: 3</p>\n						<p>When I first started using this plugin, there is a notification above that said to remove page cache or something.. There is a button directly beside (for easy access) to do that, so I clicked&#8230; It totally wiped out my entire site, wp.sghomeneeds.com doesn&#8217;t exist anymore as well.. </p>\n<p>I lost my site, don&#8217;t know where to retrieve now, and everything is wiped out. There needs to be changes as this can harm a lot of people&#8217;s sites with similar settings. </p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5:\"lawyj\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:6;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:2:{s:0:\"\";a:5:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:34:\"Permissions-Policy Security Header\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:71:\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/permissions-policy-security-header/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"Mon, 20 Dec 2021 00:26:53 PST\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:71:\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/permissions-policy-security-header/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:4:\"true\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:448:\"<p>Replies: 1</p>\n						<p>Hello,</p>\n<p>when is <strong>Permissions-Policy</strong> security header support planned for?</p>\n<p>It became a mandatory security header and sites wihout it are marked with B security grade instead of A:</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://securityheaders.com/?q=lamiacasaelettrica.com&#038;followRedirects=on\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">https://securityheaders.com/?q=lamiacasaelettrica.com&#038;followRedirects=on</a></p>\n<p>Thanks!</p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"emilianomaina\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:7;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:2:{s:0:\"\";a:5:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:41:\"Don&amp;#8217;t cache for logged in users\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:67:\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/dont-cache-for-logged-in-users/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"Sat, 18 Dec 2021 13:07:05 PST\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:67:\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/dont-cache-for-logged-in-users/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:4:\"true\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:532:\"<p>Replies: 3</p>\n						<p>Hi Marko,<br />\nMy site is a membership site.  When a non-member user (not logged in) clicks on pages, the page display is really fast.  But after a member logged in (with subscribe role), the same pages load much slower.  I already disabled &#8220;Don&#8217;t cache pages for logged in users&#8221; but have &#8220;Don&#8217;t cache pages for following user roles&#8221; enabled for Administrator.</p>\n<p>Is there any other way to make loading speed for logged in user the same as non-logged in user?</p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"francoc30\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:8;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:2:{s:0:\"\";a:5:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:136:\"&lt;span class=&quot;resolved&quot; aria-label=&quot;Resolved&quot; title=&quot;Topic is resolved.&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;301 Redirect on\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:52:\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/301-redirect-on/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"Fri, 17 Dec 2021 09:25:35 PST\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:52:\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/301-redirect-on/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:4:\"true\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1147:\"<p>Replies: 3</p>\n						<p>Hi all.<br />\nOur development team is working on troubleshooting a bug where the Page Cache is creating a 301 redirect on a webhook.</p>\n<p>Our webhook lives at an endpoint similar to domain.com/?webhook=test which POST requests are sent to via a third-party service. This works great when Page Cache is disabled, but when we enable the feature, we are getting 301 redirect responses at domain.com/?webhook=test. We are assuming that the cache is somehow picking up this url so we would like to avoid that.</p>\n<p>We&#8217;ve tried disabling Front Page cache, adding the third-party user agent to the ignore list, and we&#8217;ve also tried adding the following to Never cache the following pages:<br />\n/?webhook=test<br />\n/?webhook=*/</p>\n<p>We are also using Disk: Enhanced.</p>\n<p>We found a <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/exclude-certain-query-string/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">solution on this thread</a> that disables the plugin given a specific query parameter, but would prefer a more stable solution via w3tc if possible.</p>\n<p>Are there any other options available that we could try?</p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"seanclen\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:9;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:2:{s:0:\"\";a:5:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:153:\"&lt;span class=&quot;resolved&quot; aria-label=&quot;Resolved&quot; title=&quot;Topic is resolved.&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;Lastest Update Broke Mobile Menu\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:69:\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/lastest-update-broke-mobile-menu/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"Thu, 16 Dec 2021 17:46:39 PST\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:69:\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/lastest-update-broke-mobile-menu/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:4:\"true\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:750:\"<p>Replies: 3</p>\n						<p>My site is in three languages using Polylang plug-in.  Since the latest update of W3 Total Cache my mobile menu has broke in default language home page only.  Anyone have any ideas?  I disabled &#8220;minify&#8221; and the problem went away.  I used to use &#8220;minify&#8221; without any problems until this latest update.</p>\n\n\n<ul id=\"bbp-topic-revision-log-15171937\" class=\"bbp-topic-revision-log\">\n\n	<li id=\"bbp-topic-revision-log-15171937-item-15171949\" class=\"bbp-topic-revision-log-item\">\n		This topic was modified 1 week ago by <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/support/users/seancasey/\" title=\"View seancasey&#039;s profile\" class=\"bbp-author-link\"><span  class=\"bbp-author-name\">seancasey</span></a>.\n	</li>\n\n</ul>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"seancasey\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:10;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:2:{s:0:\"\";a:5:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:36:\"warning message for object-cache.php\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:73:\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/warning-message-for-object-cache-php/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"Thu, 16 Dec 2021 17:25:24 PST\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:73:\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/warning-message-for-object-cache-php/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:4:\"true\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1545:\"<p>Replies: 2</p>\n						<p>Hi </p>\n<p>everytime i upgrade some plugin or change the config of the w3 total cache, i am getting the warning message on the backend</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://snipboard.io/W7c6oZ.jpg\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">https://snipboard.io/W7c6oZ.jpg</a></p>\n<p>The Object Cache add-in file object-cache.php is not a W3 Total Cache drop-in. Remove it or disable Object Caching [Yes, remove it for me]</p>\n<p>I enabled redis (phpredis v5.3.4) running fine.<br />\n<a href=\"https://snipboard.io/MxArsX.jpg\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">https://snipboard.io/MxArsX.jpg</a></p>\n<p>but it keeps on asking me to remove the file and then reinstall object-cache.php file&#8230; it&#8217;s very tedious and redundant process. </p>\n<p>Is this expected behavior or I did something wrong? </p>\n<p>Please advise me on this. </p>\n<p>Thank you</p>\n\n\n<ul id=\"bbp-topic-revision-log-15171915\" class=\"bbp-topic-revision-log\">\n\n	<li id=\"bbp-topic-revision-log-15171915-item-15171921\" class=\"bbp-topic-revision-log-item\">\n		This topic was modified 1 week ago by <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/support/users/futureyoon/\" title=\"View futureyoon&#039;s profile\" class=\"bbp-author-link\"><span  class=\"bbp-author-name\">futureyoon</span></a>.\n	</li>\n	<li id=\"bbp-topic-revision-log-15171915-item-15171924\" class=\"bbp-topic-revision-log-item\">\n		This topic was modified 1 week ago by <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/support/users/futureyoon/\" title=\"View futureyoon&#039;s profile\" class=\"bbp-author-link\"><span  class=\"bbp-author-name\">futureyoon</span></a>.\n	</li>\n\n</ul>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:10:\"futureyoon\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:11;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:2:{s:0:\"\";a:5:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:153:\"&lt;span class=&quot;resolved&quot; aria-label=&quot;Resolved&quot; title=&quot;Topic is resolved.&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;Can&amp;#8217;t setup S3 For CDN\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:58:\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/cant-setup-s3-for-cdn/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"Thu, 16 Dec 2021 05:09:05 PST\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:58:\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/cant-setup-s3-for-cdn/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:4:\"true\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:2021:\"<p>Replies: 6</p>\n						<p>Can&#8217;t use S3 for a CDN with W3 Total Cache.<br />\nGeneral Settings have CDN Enabled for Amazon Simple Storage Services (S3).  I&#8217;ve created a User and set access in the CDN tab with access,secret key and bucket name. Setup IAM user with keys that worked fine when I use it with &#8216;s3cmd&#8217; to copy files to S3. Here&#8217;s the JSON:</p>\n<pre><code>{\n    &quot;Version&quot;: &quot;2012-10-17&quot;,\n    &quot;Statement&quot;: [\n        {\n            &quot;Sid&quot;: &quot;Stmt1339423675421&quot;,\n            &quot;Action&quot;: [\n                &quot;s3:DeleteObject&quot;,\n                &quot;s3:Get*&quot;,\n                &quot;s3:Put*&quot;\n            ],\n            &quot;Effect&quot;: &quot;Allow&quot;,\n            &quot;Resource&quot;: [\n                &quot;arn:aws:s3:::hellhippie&quot;,\n                &quot;arn:aws:s3:::hellhippie/*&quot;           ]\n        },\n        {\n            &quot;Sid&quot;: &quot;Stmt1339423675422&quot;,\n            &quot;Action&quot;: &quot;s3:List*&quot;,\n            &quot;Effect&quot;: &quot;Allow&quot;,\n            &quot;Resource&quot;: &quot;*&quot;\n        }\n    ]\n}</code></pre>\n<p>However, when I try the Test S3 Upload, I get the error below.  It looks like it is trying to set an ACL on the uploaded file however this should be enabled in the Put* allow in the JSON.   </p>\n<p><code>Error: Error executing &quot;PutObject&quot; on &quot;https://hellhippie.s3.us-west-1.amazonaws.com/test_s3_b75769090c596cc8e12d048908673bd6&quot;; AWS HTTP error: Client error:</code>PUT <a href=\"https://hellhippie.s3.us-west-1.amazonaws.com/test_s3_b75769090c596cc8e12d048908673bd6\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">https://hellhippie.s3.us-west-1.amazonaws.com/test_s3_b75769090c596cc8e12d048908673bd6</a><code>resulted in a</code>400 Bad Request` response: AccessControlListNotSupportedThe bucket does not all (truncated&#8230;) AccessControlListNotSupported (client): The bucket does not allow ACLs &#8211; AccessControlListNotSupported</p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"jjopllin\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:12;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:2:{s:0:\"\";a:5:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:141:\"&lt;span class=&quot;resolved&quot; aria-label=&quot;Resolved&quot; title=&quot;Topic is resolved.&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;_index_ssl.html_gzip\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:57:\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/_index_ssl-html_gzip/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"Thu, 16 Dec 2021 01:21:06 PST\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:57:\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/_index_ssl-html_gzip/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:4:\"true\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:787:\"<p>Replies: 4</p>\n						<p>Hello, </p>\n<p>This link is showing up in pageviews instead of the homepage url.</p>\n<p>/wp-content/cache/page_enhanced/edsonlegal.eu/_index_ssl.html_gzip</p>\n<p>Cache SSL (HTTPS) requests / is turned on<br />\nEnable HTTP (gzip) compression / is turned on</p>\n<p>Is this a problem with the .htacces file or do I need to make other adjustments?</p>\n<p>Thanks in advance!</p>\n\n\n<ul id=\"bbp-topic-revision-log-15169040\" class=\"bbp-topic-revision-log\">\n\n	<li id=\"bbp-topic-revision-log-15169040-item-15169045\" class=\"bbp-topic-revision-log-item\">\n		This topic was modified 1 week, 1 day ago by <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/support/users/pjvi/\" title=\"View pjvi&#039;s profile\" class=\"bbp-author-link\"><span  class=\"bbp-author-name\">pjvi</span></a>.\n	</li>\n\n</ul>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"pjvi\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:13;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:2:{s:0:\"\";a:5:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:150:\"&lt;span class=&quot;resolved&quot; aria-label=&quot;Resolved&quot; title=&quot;Topic is resolved.&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;500 Server Error for PDF file\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:66:\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/500-server-error-for-pdf-file/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"Wed, 15 Dec 2021 22:43:22 PST\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:66:\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/500-server-error-for-pdf-file/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:4:\"true\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1300:\"<p>Replies: 1</p>\n						<p>Hi!</p>\n<p>I&#8217;m a web developer and recently I&#8217;m using this plugin (PRO version) for speed optimization.</p>\n<p>From what I see, this plugin has a lot of great functionalities.</p>\n<p>Yesterday I saw something weird, let me explain you:</p>\n<p>The logged-in users have the possibility to see a PDF file when they click on a custom link with this form: DOMAIN/certificate?user_id=ID&amp;course_id=ID$nonce=TEXT</p>\n<p>After I activated the W3 Total Cache Plugin and access that page, in the output I can see a lot of random characters plus in the request has 500 status plus Content-Type: text/html; instead of application/pdf.</p>\n<p>Please tell me a solution for this issue!</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://ibb.co/hg2Vgzv\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">https://ibb.co/hg2Vgzv</a><br />\n<a href=\"https://ibb.co/xfV5mfP\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">https://ibb.co/xfV5mfP</a></p>\n\n\n<ul id=\"bbp-topic-revision-log-15168576\" class=\"bbp-topic-revision-log\">\n\n	<li id=\"bbp-topic-revision-log-15168576-item-15168580\" class=\"bbp-topic-revision-log-item\">\n		This topic was modified 1 week, 1 day ago by <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/support/users/sabingeorge/\" title=\"View Sabin Mehedin&#039;s profile\" class=\"bbp-author-link\"><span  class=\"bbp-author-name\">Sabin Mehedin</span></a>.\n	</li>\n\n</ul>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Sabin Mehedin\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:14;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:2:{s:0:\"\";a:5:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:126:\"&lt;span class=&quot;resolved&quot; aria-label=&quot;Resolved&quot; title=&quot;Topic is resolved.&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;speed\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:45:\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/speed-45/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"Wed, 15 Dec 2021 17:47:53 PST\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:45:\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/speed-45/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:4:\"true\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:766:\"<p>Replies: 7</p>\n						<p>Speed,</p>\n<p>gtmetrix loves your program.  it jacked up the performance ratings a lot.  the problem occurs with the actual speed of the site from the user point of view.  I can activate w3tc and the performance score for the site goes up, except that the actual time, using a stop watch goes down by 2-3 seconds for a total rendering time of about 9-10 seconds.  After deactivating w3tc the site has a performance speed of about 5-6 seconds to render the page, this can be anything from searches to just simply going through the site.</p>\n<p>Is there possibly something I am missing?  A setting?</p>\n<p>I have removed the program and reinstalled it.  it may have gotten about 1 second faster than the 9-10 seconds I mentioned earlier.</p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"blenkhn\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:15;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:2:{s:0:\"\";a:5:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:157:\"&lt;span class=&quot;resolved&quot; aria-label=&quot;Resolved&quot; title=&quot;Topic is resolved.&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;Is the Log4j vulnerability an issue?\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:72:\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/is-the-log4j-vulnerability-an-issue/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"Mon, 13 Dec 2021 21:10:14 PST\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:72:\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/is-the-log4j-vulnerability-an-issue/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:4:\"true\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:250:\"<p>Replies: 7</p>\n						<p>Hello,</p>\n<p>I just wanted  to check if this plugin is vulnerable to the Log4j issue that is happening right now considering I checked the plugin files and there is a .java file in the directory.</p>\n<p>Thanks a bunch!</p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"chrisweblocal\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:16;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:2:{s:0:\"\";a:5:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:58:\"Images are not loaded on Google Chrome browser, SSL issue?\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:93:\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/images-are-not-loaded-on-google-chrome-browser-ssl-issue/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"Mon, 13 Dec 2021 14:33:32 PST\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:93:\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/images-are-not-loaded-on-google-chrome-browser-ssl-issue/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:4:\"true\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4403:\"<p>Replies: 4</p>\n						<p>Hi</p>\n<p>A client for whom I work reported today that all of a sudden the images of his <strong>WooCommerce</strong> shop are not showing up on the homepage.</p>\n<p>After looking into this matter we discovered that images do show up on other browsers but <strong>not</strong> on <strong>Google Chrome</strong>. It seems that only Google Chrome all of a sudden has problems loading the images of his website.</p>\n<p>Starting to research into this, I found that the image tags have a link to <code>http://www.w3.org/...</code> as <code>src</code> attribute and that the real link of the image file is located in the <code>data-src</code> attribute. The reason for this is because of <strong>lazy loading</strong> the images on the website.</p>\n<p>On this forum I found posts about it here:<br />\n<a href=\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/after-update-no-more-images-are-displayed/page/2/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">After update NO more images are displayed!</a></p>\n<p>or here:<br />\n<a href=\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/lazy-loading-in-combination-with-the-official-amp-plugin-images-not-loading/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Lazy Loading in combination with the official amp plugin images not loading</a></p>\n<p>But I do not think it&#8217;s a problem with your plugin, I think it&#8217;s rather a problem with the <strong>outdated</strong> <code>&lt;svg&gt;</code> link which you use for the <strong>placeholder image</strong>. Therefore I would like to propose a suggestion to you:</p>\n<p>You use the following content for the <code>src</code> attribute of lazy-load <code>&lt;img&gt;</code> tags:<br />\n<code>data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=&#039;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#039;%20viewBox=&#039;0%200%20324%20324&#039;%3E%3C/svg%3E</code></p>\n<p>It&#8217;s meant to be a placeholder for images that are marked to be lazy loaded. However, this content links to the <strong>w3.org</strong> website via ordinary <code>http://</code> protocol, not <code>https://</code> protocol. The website which has the problems runs on <code>https://</code>.</p>\n<p>When a website is set up for SSL communication all links in the source code have to be <code>https://</code> protocol. If links are detected that load content via <code>http://</code> protocol the website is downgraded as <strong>&#8220;not secure&#8221;</strong>. This seems to be the reason why the loading of images fails in Google Chrome browser as soon as it finds images which have a <code>http://</code> link in their <code>src</code> attribute. Prior to that, the few images not marked for lazy-loading, are being loaded in Chrome.</p>\n<p>Servers have different configurations via <strong>.htaccess</strong> how to handle SSL traffic. Furthermore you&#8217;ll have different behavior among the various browsers how to handle such conflicts. Maybe these circumstances culminate and cause the Google Chrome browser to abort loading images as soon as it finds the first lazy-load image which contains a <code>http://</code> link in its <code>src</code> attribute because of the outdated w3.org <code>&lt;svg&gt;</code> tag.</p>\n<p>And concerning other browsers loading the images, well, the other browsers may be smart enough to recognize and consider the <code>&lt;svg&gt;</code> link to w3.org as trustworthy and not downgrade the whole website as &#8220;not secure&#8221; just because of some outdated w3.org <code>http://</code> placeholder links in <code>&lt;img&gt;</code> tags.</p>\n<p>If my assumption is correct you could solve this problem very easily. Simply update the <code>&lt;svg&gt;</code> link in the lazy-load <code>&lt;img&gt;</code> tags. You could replace this:<br />\n<code>xmlns=&#039;http://www.w3.org/2000/...</code></p>\n<p>with this:<br />\n<code>xmlns=&#039;//www.w3.org/2000/...</code></p>\n<p>This notation should avoid any <strong>SSL</strong> conflict with <strong>.htaccess</strong> configurations on production servers, since you can not predict all the different server scenarios, and it lets the server of <strong>w3.org</strong> decide how to handle the <code>HTTP</code> protocol for the placeholder image.</p>\n<p>&#8212;</p>\n<p>If this problem is already known and has been addressed then ignore this post and close it.</p>\n<p>Otherwise please let me know if my suggestion is helpful to you.</p>\n<p>Thank you for a good plugin.</p>\n<p>Sincerely,<br />\nGevorg</p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"Gevorg\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:17;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:2:{s:0:\"\";a:5:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:150:\"&lt;span class=&quot;resolved&quot; aria-label=&quot;Resolved&quot; title=&quot;Topic is resolved.&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;500 errors after 2.2.1 Update\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:66:\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/500-errors-after-2-2-1-update/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"Mon, 13 Dec 2021 12:14:58 PST\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:66:\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/500-errors-after-2-2-1-update/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:4:\"true\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:589:\"<p>Replies: 1</p>\n						<p>Updated to WP 5.8.2<br />\nUpdated W3 Cache to 2.2.1</p>\n<p>Started to get 500 Server errors on front and Admin that would go away after a refresh / reload.  Go to a few pages then suddenly 500 error again, and again etc.  </p>\n<p>I deactivated W3 and this seems to have fixed the issue on the front end of the site.  But I am still getting periodic 500 errors in the Admin. </p>\n<p>Before I go through the process of uninstalling, I was wondering if there is a potential file or setting that I can check, which would be specifically affecting the Admin area.</p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"stephwp22\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:18;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:2:{s:0:\"\";a:5:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:158:\"&lt;span class=&quot;resolved&quot; aria-label=&quot;Resolved&quot; title=&quot;Topic is resolved.&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;Converting to S3 for an existing site\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:74:\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/converting-to-s3-for-an-existing-site/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"Mon, 13 Dec 2021 10:51:39 PST\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:74:\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/converting-to-s3-for-an-existing-site/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:4:\"true\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:190:\"<p>Replies: 6</p>\n						<p>Its unclear to me from the docs whether existing files in the uploads folder will be uploaded to S3 or just newly added files. I have a lot of existing files. </p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:3:\"Hal\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:19;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:2:{s:0:\"\";a:5:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:184:\"&lt;span class=&quot;resolved&quot; aria-label=&quot;Resolved&quot; title=&quot;Topic is resolved.&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;Does the W3 WebP service work well when a staging site is used?\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:99:\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/does-the-w3-wepp-service-work-well-when-a-staging-site-is-used/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"Mon, 13 Dec 2021 07:25:58 PST\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:99:\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/does-the-w3-wepp-service-work-well-when-a-staging-site-is-used/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:4:\"true\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1058:\"<p>Replies: 1</p>\n						<p>We use a staging website and push it to the live site when updates are confirmed working well. I have converted the images on the front page of the website to WepP and the results were good on Google Sitespeed. </p>\n<p>After a few updates to the website, which are not related to the front page, the sitespeed dropped significantly and when I open the images on the front page in a new tab (or try to download straight), the jpg version is downloaded. </p>\n<p>&#8211; Does the W3 WebP service work well when a staging site is used?<br />\n&#8211; How can I confirm (make sure) that the WebP service is actually working?</p>\n<p>Thanks!</p>\n\n\n<ul id=\"bbp-topic-revision-log-15158658\" class=\"bbp-topic-revision-log\">\n\n	<li id=\"bbp-topic-revision-log-15158658-item-15158660\" class=\"bbp-topic-revision-log-item\">\n		This topic was modified 1 week, 3 days ago by <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/support/users/henksz/\" title=\"View henksz&#039;s profile\" class=\"bbp-author-link\"><span  class=\"bbp-author-name\">henksz</span></a>.\n	</li>\n\n</ul>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"henksz\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:20;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:2:{s:0:\"\";a:5:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:189:\"&lt;span class=&quot;resolved&quot; aria-label=&quot;Resolved&quot; title=&quot;Topic is resolved.&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;Page Caching does not work for Google Adwords and similar ads system\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:105:\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/page-caching-does-not-work-for-google-adwords-and-similar-ads-system/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"Thu, 09 Dec 2021 04:09:20 PST\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:105:\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/page-caching-does-not-work-for-google-adwords-and-similar-ads-system/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:4:\"true\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:739:\"<p>Replies: 2</p>\n						<p>It seems W3TC <strong>Page Cache never works</strong> for <strong>Google Adwords</strong> and similar ads systems. Does anybody notice this? </p>\n<p>The thing is that Google Ads uses GET parameters like utm_source.<br />\nI thought W3TC option &#8220;Cache URIs with query string variables&#8221; might help but it did not.</p>\n<p>One of the parameters is &#8220;gclid&#8221; which is <strong>always unique</strong> and prevents W3TC from using cache!<br />\n<a href=\"https://support.google.com/google-ads/answer/9744275?hl=en-GB\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">https://support.google.com/google-ads/answer/9744275?hl=en-GB</a></p>\n<p>Other ads platforms also use unique parameters which prevent W3TC from using Page Cache</p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:10:\"dobermann6\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:21;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:2:{s:0:\"\";a:5:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:174:\"&lt;span class=&quot;resolved&quot; aria-label=&quot;Resolved&quot; title=&quot;Topic is resolved.&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;Image Service, all images converted, but not replaced\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:88:\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/image-service-all-images-converted-but-not-replaced/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"Wed, 08 Dec 2021 12:27:02 PST\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:88:\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/image-service-all-images-converted-but-not-replaced/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:4:\"true\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1173:\"<p>Replies: 8</p>\n						<p>In the linked site there is a header picture (file <a href=\"https://eifelbienen.de/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/eifelbienen.de-biene-auf-bluete.jpg\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">https://eifelbienen.de/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/eifelbienen.de-biene-auf-bluete.jpg</a>) which is served as jpg instead of webp (I checked with dev tools) as I would expect. In media overview is shown as converted picture (see also <a href=\"https://eifelbienen.de/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/eifelbienen.de-biene-auf-bluete.webp\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">https://eifelbienen.de/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/eifelbienen.de-biene-auf-bluete.webp</a>).</p>\n<p>I have already cleared cache, but it does not change anything. I have other customer sites which have same behavior.</p>\n\n\n<ul id=\"bbp-topic-revision-log-15144958\" class=\"bbp-topic-revision-log\">\n\n	<li id=\"bbp-topic-revision-log-15144958-item-15144976\" class=\"bbp-topic-revision-log-item\">\n		This topic was modified 2 weeks, 1 day ago by <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/support/users/hfranz/\" title=\"View Heinrich Franz&#039;s profile\" class=\"bbp-author-link\"><span  class=\"bbp-author-name\">Heinrich Franz</span></a>.\n	</li>\n\n</ul>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:14:\"Heinrich Franz\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:22;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:2:{s:0:\"\";a:5:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:176:\"&lt;span class=&quot;resolved&quot; aria-label=&quot;Resolved&quot; title=&quot;Topic is resolved.&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;Wishlist count is not updated when w3tc cache is enable\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:92:\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/wishlist-count-is-not-updated-when-w3tc-cache-is-enable/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"Tue, 07 Dec 2021 21:09:07 PST\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:92:\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/wishlist-count-is-not-updated-when-w3tc-cache-is-enable/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:4:\"true\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:739:\"<p>Replies: 6</p>\n						<p>Hello,</p>\n<p>The wishlist count is not updated when I add a product to my wishlist.</p>\n<p>You can see on top right hand corner, just add a product to wishlist.<br />\nI am using YITH woocommerce wishlist plugin</p>\n<p>By contrast, when I add a product to the basket, the count is displayed correctly.</p>\n\n\n<ul id=\"bbp-topic-revision-log-15142005\" class=\"bbp-topic-revision-log\">\n\n	<li id=\"bbp-topic-revision-log-15142005-item-15142008\" class=\"bbp-topic-revision-log-item\">\n		This topic was modified 2 weeks, 2 days ago by <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/support/users/assadniang/\" title=\"View assadniang&#039;s profile\" class=\"bbp-author-link\"><span  class=\"bbp-author-name\">assadniang</span></a>.\n	</li>\n\n</ul>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:10:\"assadniang\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:23;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:2:{s:0:\"\";a:5:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:150:\"&lt;span class=&quot;resolved&quot; aria-label=&quot;Resolved&quot; title=&quot;Topic is resolved.&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;W3TC conflicts with Astra Pro\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:66:\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/w3tc-conflicts-with-astra-pro/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"Tue, 07 Dec 2021 12:34:30 PST\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:66:\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/w3tc-conflicts-with-astra-pro/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:4:\"true\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:771:\"<p>Replies: 11</p>\n						<p>Hello,<br />\nMy site uses Astra theme and its addon Astra Pro together with W3TC.  I encountered no issue until recently.  I updated Astra Pro to the latest version 3.6.3.  After that when I accessed the Customize in the dashboard, an error displayed:</p>\n<p>&#8220;PHP Fatal error:  Unknown: Cannot use output buffering in output buffering display handlers in Unknown on line 0 &#8221;</p>\n<p>After investigation, we found W3TC was causing the error.  Disabling W3TC resolved the php fatal error.</p>\n<p>We want to continue using W3TC.  But how can the error be prevented?  Is there anything can be done to fix the conflict?  Thanks</p>\n<p>Versions:<br />\nPHP 7.4.10<br />\nWP 5.8.2<br />\nAstra 3.7.5<br />\nAstra Pro 3.6.3<br />\nW3TC 2.2.0</p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"francoc30\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:24;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:2:{s:0:\"\";a:5:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:186:\"&lt;span class=&quot;resolved&quot; aria-label=&quot;Resolved&quot; title=&quot;Topic is resolved.&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;Elementor Pop-Up won&amp;#8217;t show images with W3 Cache loaded\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:91:\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/elementor-pop-up-wont-show-images-with-w3-cache-loaded/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"Tue, 07 Dec 2021 12:27:45 PST\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:91:\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/elementor-pop-up-wont-show-images-with-w3-cache-loaded/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:4:\"true\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:487:\"<p>Replies: 8</p>\n						<p>Just wanted to post this for others. No image would show in the live site using an Elementor Pop-up. The back end showed fine but the live pop-up was blank. Per another post I tried disabled a number of the options in W3 Cache Plugin. Finally I disabled the Lazy Load function and now my Pop-Up shows on the front end. I have to wonder why this only happens with W3 Cache? This happens on a number of different hosts. Just an FYI so you can fix this issue.</p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:10:\"LesTexas60\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:25;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:2:{s:0:\"\";a:5:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:207:\"&lt;span class=&quot;resolved&quot; aria-label=&quot;Resolved&quot; title=&quot;Topic is resolved.&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;Error con Safari &amp;#8220;No se pueden decodificar los datos sin procesar&amp;#8221;\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:101:\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/error-con-safari-no-se-pueden-decodificar-los-datos-sin-procesar/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"Tue, 07 Dec 2021 11:56:46 PST\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:101:\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/error-con-safari-no-se-pueden-decodificar-los-datos-sin-procesar/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:4:\"true\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:766:\"<p>Replies: 5</p>\n						<p>Hola, hace exactamente una semana, mi sitio web ecommerce comenzó a tener problemas en la  carga inicial, por lo que opté a instalar y pagar la versión Pro (suscripción anual) del plugin w3 Total cache.</p>\n<p>Al instalar y configurar el plugin todo funcionaba bien, pero me di cuenta de un detalle. Al momento se usar el navegador safari desde un iphone, al navegar por las categorías de mi tienda, provocaba el error: &#8220;Safari no puede abrir la página. El error es: &#8216;no se pueden decodificar los datos sin procesar\'&#8221;.</p>\n<p>Creo que tiene que ver con alguna configuración de caché. Favor solicito su ayuda para poder solucionar este problema, para que mis clientes no tengan problemas al navegar en mi sitio</p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:14:\"feliperamirezv\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:26;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:2:{s:0:\"\";a:5:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:147:\"&lt;span class=&quot;resolved&quot; aria-label=&quot;Resolved&quot; title=&quot;Topic is resolved.&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;Cannot select Opcode Cache\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:63:\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/cannot-select-opcode-cache/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"Mon, 06 Dec 2021 23:39:52 PST\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:63:\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/cannot-select-opcode-cache/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:4:\"true\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:347:\"<p>Replies: 1</p>\n						<p>Hello,</p>\n<p>I am with Bluehost on a shared hosting.</p>\n<p>I check the compatibility test, and it showed that:<br />\nOpcode cache: PHP6 (Green)<br />\nMemcached extension: Not available<br />\nMemcache extension: Not available<br />\nRedis extension: Not available</p>\n<p>But under Opcode Cache, it says Not Available</p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:10:\"assadniang\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:27;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:2:{s:0:\"\";a:5:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:170:\"&lt;span class=&quot;resolved&quot; aria-label=&quot;Resolved&quot; title=&quot;Topic is resolved.&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;So the pages are not cached until you visit them?\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:85:\"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/so-the-pages-are-not-cached-until-you-visit-them/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"Mon, 06 Dec 2021 23:07:25 PST\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0